  "chapter": {
    "number": 48,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Israel’s Stubbornness"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Listen to this, O house of Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you who are called by the name of Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who have descended from the line of Judah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who swear by the name of the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who invoke the God of Israel—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but not in truth or righteousness—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who indeed call yourselves after the holy city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and lean on the God of Israel;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD of Hosts is His name.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I foretold the former things long ago;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they came out of My mouth and I proclaimed them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Suddenly I acted, and they came to pass.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I knew that you are stubborn;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your neck is iron and your forehead is bronze.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I declared it to you long ago;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I announced it before it came to pass,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you could not claim, ‘My idol has done this;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my carved image and molten god has ordained it.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have heard these things; look at them all.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will you not acknowledge them?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "From now on I will tell you of new things,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "hidden things unknown to you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are created now, and not long ago;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have not heard of them before today.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "So you cannot claim,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘I already knew them!’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You have never heard; you have never understood;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for a long time your ears have not been open.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For I knew how deceitful you are;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have been called a rebel from birth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the sake of My name I will delay My wrath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the sake of My praise I will restrain it,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you will not be cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "See, I have refined you, but not as silver;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have tested you in the furnace of affliction.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For My own sake, My very own sake, I will act;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for how can I let Myself be defamed?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will not yield My glory to another.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Deliverance Promised to Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen to Me, O Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Israel, whom I have called:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I am He; I am the first,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I am the last.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely My own hand founded the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My right hand spread out the heavens;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "when I summon them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they stand up together.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Come together, all of you, and listen:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Which of the idols has foretold these things?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The LORD’s chosen ally will carry out His desire against Babylon,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and His arm will be against the Chaldeans.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2675
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I, even I, have spoken;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yes, I have called him.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have brought him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he will succeed in his mission.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Come near to Me and listen to this:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "From the beginning I have not spoken in secret;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the time it happened, I was there.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "And now the Lord GOD has sent me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "accompanied by His Spirit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD your Redeemer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Holy One of Israel:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am the LORD your God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who teaches you for your benefit,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who directs you in the way you should go.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If only you had paid attention to My commandments,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your peace would have been like a river,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and your righteousness like waves of the sea.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your descendants would have been as countless as the sand,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your offspring as numerous as its grains;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2676
          },
          {
            "text": "their name would never be cut off",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or eliminated from My presence.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Leave Babylon!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Flee from the Chaldeans!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Declare it with a shout of joy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "proclaim it,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "let it go out to the ends of the earth, saying,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“The LORD has redeemed His servant Jacob!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They did not thirst when He led them through the deserts;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He made water flow for them from the rock;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He split the rock, and water gushed out.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“There is no peace,” says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“for the wicked.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 2675,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, the Babylonians; also in verse 20",
